        "entry_id": "08be7d75-34eb-472c-8cbf-9beab9f1ab3d",
        "essay_identifier": "What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skill",
        "raw_text": "Understanding the technology that constantly surrounds us and the way each of its components interacts with each other as a part of a\nlarger system excites me the most. Learning about the inner mechanisms of this sphere has always fascinated me. Engineering is a lucrative\ncareer with impressive prospects and a diverse selection of \ufb01elds to work in. The rapid developments in this domain, which necessitate\ncontinuous learning, critical thinking, and problem solving, are ideal for fostering both professional and personal growth. The last two years I\nspent preparing for the competitive exams have inculcated a habit of hard work, discipline, and e\ufb00ectively utilizing my time. It has prepared\nme to face challenges, try out di\ufb00erent approaches, and learn from my failures. I am highly motivated, eager to learn, and willing to push my\nlimits. This mindset is my greatest strength, which hopefully is suitable for the program.\n",
